    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-05-28T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-05-28T03:00:00-05:00" n="612"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d612">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 300.115N27/8</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">
                        <gloss type="from">The Consul</gloss> at Liverpool</hi> (<hi rend="italic"
                        >Washington</hi>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Liverpool</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-05-28T08:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 28, 1915, 8 a. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 8.15 a. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Nebraskan</hi> chartered White Star Line, water ballast. Shock
                    followed by explosion 8.24 evening May 25, latitude 51.14 N., longitude 10.52 W.
                    Captain and officer watch say flag lowered ten minutes before explosion. Chief
                    engineer only person saw track approaching torpedo. Captain, officer watch, and
                    chief engineer say light time explosion sufficient see two thousand feet. Name
                    and port painted both sides letters six feet high. Lieutenant Towers,
                    Constructor McBride making further examination <hi rend="italic">Nebraskan</hi>
                    to-day. They will photograph in dry dock next week.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
